MORA TSP SCNARIO 3.2.1 ONE CORE ALLOCATION TO A SINGLE PARTITION

One partition is continuously running on a dedicated core while other partitions can share rest of the
cores.

        25ms | 25ms | 25ms | 25ms | 25ms | 25ms | 25ms | 25ms | 25ms | 25ms |
Core0 | <---------------------------- P0 ---------------------------------> |
Core1 | <P1> | <--- P2 --> | <--- P3 --> | <P4> | <P2> | <------ P5 ------> |
Core2 |                                                                     |
Core3 |                                                                     |

P0 - IO
P1 - Mission Manager
P2 - Thermal Control
P3 - Power Control
P4 - AOCS
P5 - Payload

Partitions P2, P3, and P5 need to define CONFIGURE_MAXIMUM_SEMAPHORES in rtems_config.h after configure.
Ex: #define CONFIGURE_MAXIMUM_SEMAPHORES 1

